    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1930-03-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1930-03-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="66"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d66">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15a3/768a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Castle</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1930-03-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 20, 1930—6 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>54. You may emphasize the following: After conference with leaders, we are
                    convinced that present naval proposals to Japan are all it would be possible for
                    us to attempt to carry. Alternative is full twenty-three cruiser program.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Cotton</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
